{"title_page": "List of Modern Family episodes", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Modern Family'' episodes}}\n[[File:Modern Family Title.svg|right|300px]]\n\n''[[Modern Family]]'' is an American family, [[mockumentary]] [[television comedy|comedy series]] that aired on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]. It was created by [[Christopher Lloyd (TV producer)|Christopher Lloyd]] and [[Steven Levitan]]. The show follows the family lives of Jay Pritchett ([[Ed O'Neill]]), his daughter Claire Dunphy ([[Julie Bowen]]), and his son Mitchell Pritchett ([[Jesse Tyler Ferguson]]), who all live in [[Los Angeles]]. Claire is married to Phil Dunphy ([[Ty Burrell]]). They have three children: Haley ([[Sarah Hyland]]), Alex ([[Ariel Winter]]) and Luke ([[Nolan Gould]]). Jay is married to a much younger [[Colombian Americans|Colombian]] woman, Gloria ([[Sof\u00eda Vergara]]), and is helping her raise her teenage son, Manny ([[Rico Rodriguez (actor)|Rico Rodriguez]]) along with their new baby Fulgencio \"Joe\" Pritchett ([[Jeremy Maguire]]). Mitchell and his husband Cameron Tucker ([[Eric Stonestreet]]) have an [[International adoption|adopted]] [[Vietnamese people|Vietnamese]] child, Lily Tucker-Pritchett ([[Aubrey Anderson-Emmons]]). The series premiered on September 23, 2009 and concluded on April 8, 2020.\n\nOver the course of 11 seasons, 250 episodes of ''Modern Family'' aired.\n\n==Series overview==\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n| infoA      = Rank\n| infoB      = Viewers<br>(in millions)\n\n| color1     = #FB680D\n| link1      = <includeonly>List of Modern Family episodes</includeonly>#Season 1 (2009\u201310)\n| episodes1  = 24\n| start1     = {{Start date|2009|9|23}}\n| end1       = {{End date|2010|5|19}}\n| infoA1     = 36\n| infoB1     = 9.49<ref name=\"tvhit\">Andreeva, Nellie. (May 27, 2010) [https://www.deadline.com/2010/05/full-series-rankings-for-the-2009-10-broadcast-season Full Series Rankings For The 2009-10 Br